<font color="#FFFFFF">'''TIMEWARP SYNDROME''' is the '''30<sup>th</sup> phenomenon''' that has been documented in '''[[The Backrooms]]'''. This phenomenon is also between '''[[Phenomenon 29]]''' and '''[[Phenomenon 31]]'''.</font>
==<span style="font-size:45px;"><font color="#FFFFFF">> Description</font></span>==
<big><big><big>If any of your devices stop working.. you're screwed.</big></big></big>
----
<div style="text-align:left;">
{{Blurimage Border|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=hubexdgdex|text-color=white|caption=An aftermath of a watch experiencing the Timewarp Syndrome.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=1.0|file=20Watch.png}}
<font color="#FFFFFF">'''Phenomenon 30''', also often referred to as "TIMEWARP SYNDROME", "TEMPORAL CORRUPTION" or "CHRONOPHAGE", is an extremely rare and perilous phenomenon which can be found on time-based/time travel levels (e.g., [[Level 80]], etc.) '''Phenomenon 20''' can occur at any time and at any moment, even when you don't expect it.

'''Phenomenon 30''' is a phenomenon that can randomly brick/break any devices found in that specific level. If they don't brick, then they glitch out and produce static and strange noises. Some wanderers report that they can hear screaming and muffling, as someone is tied up and about to be killed.

{{Blurimage Border|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=hubexdgdex|text-color=white|caption=An example of a [[Backchat (Collaborative Log)|Backchat]] error.|hovertext=I don't know how it turned low quality??? Sorry for that.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=2.0|file=Zrscatrev.png}}
'''Phenomenon 30''' cannot break any [[Backchat (Collaborative Log)|Backchat]] devices for unknown reasons. Some Backchat devices can flash white, while others display cursed, unreadable Egyptian hieroglyphics. Some images posted on corrupted [[Backchat (Collaborative Log)|Backchat]] devices can turn into strange symbols and static, or a random cartoon/show you watched when you were a kid.

It will be distorted and look off. After an episode/part ends, a strange ticking clock will appear behind the character, and the clock will tick. The background will turn orange and non-saturated, and orange-like mist or dust will surround the screen. The clock ticks fast. When the clock reaches 12:00 am, everything turns black except the character and the clock, leaving a faint white glow behind.
==Overloading==
{{Blurimage Border|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=hubexdgdex|text-color=white|caption=An example of the Timewarp Syndrome being overloaded taken from [[Level 80]]. You can see a bright light coming from windows, as a yellow-like mist surrounds the whole area.|hovertext=Do people even read these? Be honest.|𝚏𝚒𝚐=4.0|file=AI lolololol.png}}

Sometimes, '''Phenomenon 30''' can overload very rarely. When the overloading effect happens, the whole level shakes and windows emit a yellow-like mist. All devices you have will explode, then every object/architecture will get sucked into the window. After it overloads, a white-like glow will cover your eyes, then you will wake up on the same level, except that every room/area looks empty.

When you leave that certain level, every level you enter from now on will appear empty and dilapidated, as the whole [[The Backrooms|Backrooms]] got ruined. '''Phenomenon 30''' lastly makes a wanderer feel electric shocks in their body. Your insides can also overload; surprisingly, this doesn't kill you. Eternal torture.
==Discovery==
It is unknown how this phenomenon got created, as it was created when [[Level 0]] was created.
